  "title": "Purchaser #79034",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction Industry</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Purchaser</strong></li><li>Working Location: West - Tuas Crescent (Company transport provided)</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days (Mon - Fri: 8 am - 5 pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to SGD 3800 + Allowances + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Source and purchase construction equipment, spare parts, and supplies in line with operational requirements.</li><li>Request and assess supplier quotations to ensure optimal balance of cost, delivery time, and product quality.</li><li>Engage in vendor negotiations covering pricing, delivery timelines, payment terms, and contract conditions.</li><li>Generate and dispatch purchase orders, track shipments to confirm timely arrival of goods.</li><li>Keep detailed and up-to-date procurement documentation, including vendor profiles, cost data, and delivery benchmarks.</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams to forecast and meet material demands efficiently.</li><li>Supervise stock levels to avoid shortages or excessive inventory.</li><li>Review supplier performance and initiate corrective actions or enhancements when necessary.</li><li>Monitor industry developments, product innovations, and alternative sourcing opportunities.</li><li>Address and resolve issues related to late deliveries, quality discrepancies, or supplier non-compliance.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of hands-on experience in purchasing or procurement, ideally within equipment rental, maintenance, or industrial sectors.</li><li>Good knowledge of sourcing procedures for machinery, spare components, and technical materials.</li><li>Proven skills in negotiation, supplier relations, and data analysis.</li><li>Competent in Microsoft Excel, Outlook, and procurement or P2P software platforms.</li><li>Effective communicator with strong coordination and problem-solving capabilities.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79034 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
